<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by lar on 08-06-2001 07:03 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Hi,

If I'm not mistaking, Sickboy mentioned

&gt;&gt;Since some territories do not put a product in a Europ- /Sierra-Box on the shelves we have to release it in a DVD-packaging but with CD-ROMs in the inside&lt;&lt;

The keyword here is "Some territories." 

It's sad but true that in the UK for instance it's getting really hard to get your game even in the shelves if it's not in a DVD box, and you'll never get large quantities of your game there if it's not in such a box. Not our choice, but the choice of the retailers and of the market apparently. CDV would be doing the wrong thing by not putting it in a DVD box for those territories, as it would most definitely result in lesser sales. I don't know how it is in Germany, but I guess the evolution is the same like in the other countries. This has nothing to do with not listening to fans or so, but everything with the dictatoriate of the retailers.

Lar

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
